		<div class="container mx-auto px-4">
			<div class="text-center mb-12">
				<div class="flex items-center justify-center mb-4">
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent mr-4"></div>
					<h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary font-heading">HOW ELECTRIC FURNACES WORK</h2>
					<div class="w-10 h-1 bg-accent ml-4"></div>
				</div>
				<p class="text-lg text-darkgray max-w-3xl mx-auto">
					Understanding how your electric furnace operates can help you make informed decisions about maintenance and
					repairs.
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-lg shadow-md max-w-4xl mx-auto">
				<div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 items-center">
					<div>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">The Heating Process</h3>
						<ol class="space-y-4 text-darkgray">
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">1</span>
								<p><strong>Thermostat Signal:</strong> When your home's temperature drops below the thermostat setting,
									it sends a signal to the furnace to start the heating cycle.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">2</span>
								<p><strong>Heating Elements Activate:</strong> Electricity flows through the heating elements, causing
									them to heat up, similar to how a toaster works.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">3</span>
								<p><strong>Air Circulation:</strong> The blower motor pushes air across the hot heating elements,
									warming the air.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">4</span>
								<p><strong>Distribution:</strong> The warm air is distributed throughout your home via the ductwork.</p>
							</li>
							<li class="flex">
								<span
									class="bg-secondary text-white rounded-full w-8 h-8 flex items-center justify-center font-bold mr-4 flex-shrink-0">5</span>
								<p><strong>Cycle Continues:</strong> This process continues until your home reaches the desired
									temperature set on the thermostat.</p>
							</li>
						</ol>
					</div>

					<div>
						<h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary mb-6">Key Components</h3>
						<ul class="space-y-3 text-darkgray">
							<li class="flex items-start">
								<svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" class="h-5 w-5 text-accent mr-2 mt-0.5 flex-shrink-0"
